  <!-- JET LAG TIPS -->
  <div class="jetlag-tips-section" id="jetlag-tips">
    <div class="jetlag-tips-inner">
      <div class="section-label">// beating the clock</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; color:var(--text-main);">Jet Lag<br><span style="color:var(--neon-blue); text-shadow:var(--glow-blue);">Tips &amp; Hacks</span></h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Science-backed strategies and Tokyo-specific tricks for resetting your internal clock. The average traveler from the US takes 5-7 days to fully adjust. These tips can cut that in half.</p>

      <div class="jetlag-tips-grid">
        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">🌅</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">Light Exposure Strategy</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            Your circadian clock is controlled by light. <strong>Get outside by 7AM Tokyo time</strong> — even 15 minutes of morning sunlight dramatically accelerates adjustment. Avoid bright screens after 9PM if you are trying to sleep. If you flew from the West Coast, seek morning light and avoid afternoon light for the first 2 days. From Europe, the opposite: afternoon light is your friend.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">🍜</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">Eat on Tokyo Time</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            Meal timing is the second-most powerful circadian signal after light. <strong>Force yourself to eat breakfast at 7-8AM Tokyo time</strong>, even if you are not hungry. A Japanese morning set (teishoku) — rice, grilled fish, miso soup, pickles — is ideal. Avoid heavy meals after 9PM. Your gut has its own clock, and resetting it through regular Tokyo-time meals speeds whole-body adjustment.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">💊</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">Melatonin Timing</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            If you use melatonin, timing matters more than dose. Take <strong>0.5-1mg at 9PM Tokyo time</strong> starting 2 days before your flight. Low dose is key — more is not better and can cause grogginess. Available at Japanese drugstores (look for メラトニン at Don Quijote or Amazon.co.jp). Combine with dimming lights and a warm bath (try an onsen) 2 hours before your target bedtime.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">🚫</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">The Nap Trap</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            The 3PM nap is the enemy. It feels necessary. It is catastrophic. <strong>If you must nap, set a hard alarm for 20 minutes</strong> and nap before 2PM only. Sleeping 2+ hours in the afternoon guarantees another sleepless night. Instead: go outside, walk to a konbini, splash cold water on your face. The afternoon crash is temporary — push through and you will sleep that night.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">♨️</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">The Onsen Reset</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            A hot bath 90 minutes before bedtime signals your body to cool down, triggering sleepiness. Tokyo's 24-hour onsen (like <strong>Thermae-Yu in Shinjuku</strong>) are perfect for this. The drop in core body temperature after soaking promotes deep sleep. Even a regular hot hotel bath works. Pro tip: alternate between hot bath and cool rinse for maximum effect.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">🏃</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">Move Your Body</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            Morning exercise outdoors is a circadian reset double-hit: light exposure plus physical activity. <strong>Walk 30 minutes before 9AM</strong> — Meiji Shrine forest, Ueno Park, Yoyogi Park, or just around your hotel neighborhood. Exercise also reduces the inflammation that makes jet lag worse. Avoid intense workouts after 6PM as they can delay sleep onset.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">☕</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">Caffeine Strategy</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            Use caffeine strategically, not desperately. <strong>Coffee before noon Tokyo time only.</strong> After that, switch to green tea (lower caffeine, plus L-theanine for calm alertness). Japan's convenience store coffee is surprisingly excellent — 7-Eleven's ¥100 drip is better than most chains. For emergency alertness after noon, try matcha — the caffeine curve is gentler and will not wreck your evening sleep.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="jt-card">
          <div class="jt-card-icon">🌙</div>
          <div class="jt-card-title">24-Hour Spots for 2-5AM</div>
          <div class="jt-card-body">
            When sleep will not come, do not fight it — explore. <strong>Key 24-hour lifelines:</strong> Ichiran Ramen (solo booths, no judgment), Thermae-Yu (onsen + rest area), Don Quijote (shopping chaos), any konbini (food + drinks + WiFi), manga kissa/internet cafes (private booth + recliner + unlimited drinks for ~¥1,500). Karaoke chains (private room + drinks). The city always has somewhere for the sleepless.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="neon-line" aria-hidden="true"></div>
  <!-- SURVIVAL TIPS -->
  <section class="tips-section" id="survive" style="max-width:100%; padding:6rem 2.5rem;">
    <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto;">
      <div class="section-label">// staying sane at 3am</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; color:var(--text-main);">Jet Lag<br><span style="color:var(--neon-blue); text-shadow:var(--glow-blue);">Survival Guide</span></h2>

      <div class="tips-grid">
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">01</div>
          <div class="tip-title">Don't fight it</div>
          <div class="tip-body">The worst thing you can do is lie in bed angry at the ceiling. If you're awake, Tokyo wants you. Get dressed. Go outside. The city is different at night and you have earned this view.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">02</div>
          <div class="tip-title">Konbini is your friend</div>
          <div class="tip-body">7-Eleven, Lawson, and Family Mart are not just convenience stores. They are restaurants, pharmacies, ATMs, and community centers. The onigiri is fresh every few hours. Get one at 2AM.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">03</div>
          <div class="tip-title">The Last Train &amp; Taxi Apps</div>
          <div class="tip-body">Trains stop around 12:30AM and restart around 5AM. No night buses in central Tokyo. Your options: <strong style="color:var(--neon-blue)">GO</strong> (Japan's #1 taxi app) or <strong style="color:var(--neon-blue)">S.RIDE</strong> (one-slide hailing). Both accept credit cards. Budget ¥3,000–5,000 for a late-night ride.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">04</div>
          <div class="tip-title">Sunlight resets the clock</div>
          <div class="tip-body">Get outside by 7AM. Sunlight is the most powerful circadian reset. Even 20 minutes of morning sun — especially in a park — will shift your body clock faster than any supplement.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">05</div>
          <div class="tip-title">Avoid the nap trap</div>
          <div class="tip-body">The long afternoon nap is tempting and catastrophic. If you must sleep, set an alarm for 20 minutes. Sleeping 2+ hours in the afternoon guarantees you'll be awake until 4AM again.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="tip-item">
          <div class="tip-number">06</div>
          <div class="tip-title">Eat on Tokyo time</div>
          <div class="tip-body">Your body syncs to local time partly through meal timing. Even if you're not hungry, eat breakfast when Tokyo eats breakfast. Find a morning teishoku set. Signal to your body that this is now.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <div class="neon-line" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <!-- TAXI APP SECTION -->
  <section class="taxi-section" id="taxi">
    <div style="max-width:1200px; margin:0 auto;">
      <div class="section-label">// getting around after midnight</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; color:var(--text-main);">Taxi Apps<br><span style="color:var(--neon-blue); text-shadow:var(--glow-blue);">for 2AM</span></h2>
      <p style="font-size:0.78rem; color:var(--text-dim); max-width:600px; line-height:1.8; margin-bottom:3rem;">
        Trains stop around 12:30AM and don't restart until 5AM. No night buses in central Tokyo. These apps are your lifeline.
      </p>

      <div class="taxi-grid">
        <div class="taxi-card">
          <div class="taxi-card-icon icon-go">GO</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-rank">// #1 recommended</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-name">GO</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-tagline">Japan's most popular taxi app</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-body">
            Largest fleet in Japan. AI-powered dispatch finds the nearest cab in seconds. Pay with credit card in-app. Available nationwide. <strong style="color:var(--neon-blue)">Download before your trip.</strong> Interface in English.
          </div>
          <div class="taxi-card-links">
            <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/go-taxi/id1476075498" target="_blank">App Store</a>
            <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=jp.goinc.s2" target="_blank">Google Play</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="taxi-card">
          <div class="taxi-card-icon icon-sride">S</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-rank">// tokyo specialist</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-name">S.RIDE</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-tagline">One-slide hailing, big in Tokyo</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-body">
            Slide to hail — one gesture. Backed by Sony. Strong coverage in central Tokyo, especially Shinjuku/Shibuya/Roppongi. Credit card in-app. English support. Often faster than GO in Shinjuku.
          </div>
          <div class="taxi-card-links">
            <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/s-ride/id1456498047" target="_blank">App Store</a>
            <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=jp.sride.app" target="_blank">Google Play</a>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="taxi-card">
          <div class="taxi-card-icon icon-uber">U</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-rank">// backup option</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-name">Uber</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-tagline">You know it. It works here too.</div>
          <div class="taxi-card-body">
            Familiar interface, no new app to learn. Works in Tokyo but has fewer cars than GO or S.RIDE — expect longer wait times after midnight. Prices tend to run slightly higher. Good as backup.
          </div>
          <div class="taxi-card-links">
            <a href="https://apps.apple.com/app/uber/id368677368" target="_blank">App Store</a>
            <a href="https://play.google.com/store/apps/details?id=com.ubercab" target="_blank">Google Play</a>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="taxi-tip">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Budget <strong>&#165;3,000-5,000</strong> for a late-night ride across central Tokyo. Shinjuku→Shibuya ~¥2,000. Late-night surcharge (22:00-05:00) adds ~20%. Download GO and S.RIDE before you land — setup requires SMS verification. If all apps fail at 3AM, walk to any major hotel entrance — taxis queue there.
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>


  <div class="neon-line" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <!-- GETTING AROUND -->
  <div class="getting-around-section" id="getting-around">
    <div class="getting-around-inner">
      <div class="section-label">// navigating the world's best transit</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; color:var(--text-main);">Getting<br><span style="color:var(--neon-blue); text-shadow:var(--glow-blue);">Around Tokyo</span></h2>
      <p class="section-desc">Tokyo's transit system is the most efficient in the world. Once you understand the basics, getting anywhere is trivially easy — except between midnight and 5AM.</p>

      <div class="ga-grid">
        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">🚃</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">Trains &amp; Metro</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            <strong>JR Yamanote Line</strong> is the green circle line connecting all major stations (Shinjuku, Shibuya, Ikebukuro, Tokyo, Ueno, Akihabara). Runs 4:30AM-1AM. <strong>Tokyo Metro</strong> covers everywhere else with 13 lines. Google Maps works perfectly for route planning — just search origin to destination. First train ~5AM, last train ~midnight. Trains are on time to the second.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">💳</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">Suica / Pasmo IC Cards</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            Get a <strong>Suica card</strong> (JR) or <strong>Pasmo</strong> (Metro) — they work on all trains, buses, and most vending machines and konbini. Now available digitally in <strong>Apple Wallet</strong> and Google Pay — set it up before landing. Charge at any station machine or in-app. Tap in, tap out. No paper tickets needed. Also works at 7-Eleven, FamilyMart, Lawson, taxis, coin lockers, and vending machines.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">🚕</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">Taxis After Midnight</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            Last trains leave around <strong>12:30AM</strong>. First trains restart at <strong>5AM</strong>. Between those hours, your options are: <strong>GO app</strong> (largest fleet, best), <strong>S.RIDE</strong> (one-slide hailing, strong in central Tokyo), or <strong>Uber</strong> (fewer cars, higher prices). Budget ¥3,000-5,000 for cross-city rides. Late-night surcharge adds ~20% between 10PM-5AM. Download and set up apps before you arrive — they require SMS verification.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">🚶</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">Walking Tokyo</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            Tokyo is incredibly walkable and <strong>extremely safe at all hours</strong>. Many of the best neighborhoods (Shimokitazawa, Nakameguro, Yanaka) are best explored on foot. Distances between stations in central Tokyo are often 10-15 minutes on foot. At 3AM, the empty streets are yours — walking from Shibuya to Shinjuku takes about 30 minutes and is beautiful at night. Convenience stores every few blocks if you need a break.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">📱</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">Essential Apps</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            <strong>Google Maps</strong> — transit directions are perfect in Tokyo. <strong>GO</strong> — taxi hailing (#1 in Japan). <strong>S.RIDE</strong> — backup taxi app. <strong>Google Translate</strong> — camera mode reads Japanese signs in real-time. <strong>Tabelog</strong> — Japan's most trusted restaurant rating (3.5+ is excellent). <strong>Navitime</strong> — detailed train schedules and platform numbers. All work on mobile data or pocket WiFi.
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="ga-card">
          <div class="ga-card-icon">📶</div>
          <div class="ga-card-title">WiFi &amp; SIM</div>
          <div class="ga-card-body">
            Get an <strong>eSIM before landing</strong> — providers like Ubigi, Airalo, or Mobal offer Japan data plans from ¥1,000/week. Alternatively, <strong>pocket WiFi</strong> rental is available at Narita/Haneda airports. Free WiFi exists at all konbini, Starbucks, and many train stations but is slow. Your hotel WiFi will be fast. Having constant data access is essential for maps, translation, and taxi apps — do not rely on free WiFi alone.
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ga-protip">
        <strong>Pro tip:</strong> Airport to city: <strong>Narita Express (N'EX)</strong> to Shinjuku/Shibuya/Tokyo Station (~60 min, ¥3,250). <strong>Haneda</strong> is much closer — Keikyu or Tokyo Monorail to central Tokyo (~20-30 min, ¥300-500). If arriving late at night when trains are not running, taxi from Haneda costs ¥5,000-8,000; from Narita, budget ¥20,000+ (take the Limousine Bus instead, ~¥3,200, runs until late). Buy your Suica/Pasmo at the airport before leaving.
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- TIME SLIDER -->
  <div class="time-slider-section" id="now">
    <div class="time-slider-inner">
      <div class="section-label">// what can you do right now</div>
      <h2 class="section-title" style="font-family:'Bebas Neue',sans-serif; color:var(--text-main);">It's <span id="sliderTimeDisplay" style="color:var(--neon-blue); text-shadow:var(--glow-blue);">--:--</span><br>in Tokyo</h2>

      <div class="slider-wrap">
        <input type="range" class="time-range" id="timeSlider" min="0" max="23" step="1" value="2" aria-label="Select hour in Tokyo (0-23)" aria-valuemin="0" aria-valuemax="23" aria-valuenow="2" aria-valuetext="02:00 Tokyo time">
        <div class="slider-labels">
          <span>12AM</span><span>3AM</span><span>6AM</span><span>9AM</span>
          <span>12PM</span><span>3PM</span><span>6PM</span><span>9PM</span><span>11PM</span>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div style="margin-bottom:1.5rem;">
        <button class="time-now-badge" id="tokyoNowBtn" type="button" aria-label="Set slider to current Tokyo time">▶ SET TO TOKYO NOW</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tip-cards" id="timeTipCards"></div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="neon-line" aria-hidden="true"></div>

  <footer role="contentinfo">
    <div class="footer-logo">TokyoJetLag.com</div>
    <div class="footer-sub">
      For the wide-awake, the displaced, and the thoroughly confused.<br>
      Tokyo · 東京 · All hours · All nights
    </div>

    <div class="footer-about">
      <div class="footer-about-title">About Tokyo Jet Lag</div>
      <div class="footer-about-text">
        Tokyo Jet Lag was born at 3AM in a Shinjuku convenience store, staring at an onigiri selection and wondering why nobody had made a guide for people like us — the wide-awake, time-displaced visitors who find themselves wandering Tokyo's streets when the rest of the world is asleep. Every venue is hand-picked. Every hour is verified. This is not a travel blog. This is a survival guide for your circadian system's worst nightmare and Tokyo's best-kept secret: the city after dark.
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="footer-social" aria-label="Social media links">
      <a href="#" aria-label="Instagram" title="Instagram">📷</a>
      <a href="#" aria-label="Twitter / X" title="Twitter / X">𝕏</a>
      <a href="#" aria-label="TikTok" title="TikTok">🎵</a>
      <a href="#" aria-label="YouTube" title="YouTube">▶</a>
    </div>

    <div class="footer-contact">
      <a href="mailto:hello@tokyojetlag.com">hello@tokyojetlag.com</a> · Tokyo, Japan
    </div>

    <div style="margin-top:1rem;"></div>
    <div class="footer-disclaimer">
      Hours and venue info are updated periodically but Tokyo never stops changing. Always verify hours directly before visiting. We are not responsible for closed restaurants at 3AM — that is between you and your jet lag. Venue data last verified March 2026.
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script>
  (function() {
    'use strict';

    // ─── REDUCED MOTION CHECK ───
    var prefersReducedMotion = window.matchMedia('(prefers-reduced-motion: reduce)').matches;

    // ─── DOM CACHE ───
    var $ = function(sel) { return document.querySelector(sel); };
    var $$ = function(sel) { return document.querySelectorAll(sel); };

    var dom = {
      heroVideo:      $('#heroVideo'),
      heroImgBg:      $('#heroImgBg'),
      visitorClock:   $('#visitorClock'),
      worldClock:     $('#worldClock'),
      particles:      $('#particles'),
      areaNav:        $('#areaNav'),
      areaNavWrap:    $('#areaNavWrap'),
      timeSlider:     $('#timeSlider'),
      sliderDisplay:  $('#sliderTimeDisplay'),
      timeTipCards:   $('#timeTipCards'),
      tokyoNowBtn:    $('#tokyoNowBtn'),
      cityCanvas:     $('#cityCanvas'),
    };

    // ─── TIME-BASED VIDEO SWITCHING ───
    var VIDEO_SOURCES = {
      morning: 'https://videos.pexels.com/video-files/4434242/4434242-sd_640_360_24fps.mp4',
      day:     'https://videos.pexels.com/video-files/2614602/2614602-sd_640_360_25fps.mp4',
      night:   'https://videos.pexels.com/video-files/3942468/3942468-sd_640_360_30fps.mp4',
    };

    var BG_FALLBACKS = {
      morning: 'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1540959733332-eab4deabeeaf?w=1200&q=60',
      day:     'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1503899036084-c55cdd92da26?w=1200&q=60',
      night:   'https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1542051841857-5f90071e7989?w=1200&q=60',
    };

    function getTokyoHour() {
      return parseInt(new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
        hour: 'numeric', hour12: false, timeZone: 'Asia/Tokyo'
      }).format(new Date()));
    }

    function getTimeOfDay(hour) {
      if (hour >= 5 && hour < 12) return 'morning';
      if (hour >= 12 && hour < 18) return 'day';
      return 'night';
    }

    function loadTimeBasedVideo() {
      var tokyoHour = getTokyoHour();
      var tod = getTimeOfDay(tokyoHour);
      var video = dom.heroVideo;
      var imgBg = dom.heroImgBg;

      imgBg.style.backgroundImage = "url('" + BG_FALLBACKS[tod] + "')";

      if (prefersReducedMotion) {
        imgBg.style.opacity = '0.25';
        return;
      }

      var src = VIDEO_SOURCES[tod];
      video.innerHTML = '<source src="' + src + '" type="video/mp4">';
      video.load();

      video.addEventListener('canplaythrough', function() {
        video.classList.add('loaded');
        imgBg.style.opacity = '0';
      }, { once: true });

      video.addEventListener('error', function() {
        imgBg.style.opacity = '0.25';
      });

      setInterval(function() {
        var newTod = getTimeOfDay(getTokyoHour());
        if (newTod !== tod) location.reload();
      }, 15 * 60 * 1000);
    }

    loadTimeBasedVideo();

    // ─── VISITOR TIMEZONE ───
    (function() {
      var tz = Intl.DateTimeFormat().resolvedOptions().timeZone;
      var now = new Date();
      var fmtLocal = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
        hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit', hour12: true, timeZone: tz
      }).format(now);
      var fmtTokyo = new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
        hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit', hour12: true, timeZone: 'Asia/Tokyo'
      }).format(now);
      var tokyoH = getTokyoHour();

      var tzCity = {
        'America/Los_Angeles': 'Los Angeles', 'America/New_York': 'New York',
        'America/Chicago': 'Chicago', 'America/Denver': 'Denver',
        'America/Vancouver': 'Vancouver', 'America/Toronto': 'Toronto',
        'Europe/London': 'London', 'Europe/Paris': 'Paris',
        'Europe/Berlin': 'Berlin', 'Europe/Rome': 'Rome',
        'Asia/Seoul': 'Seoul', 'Asia/Shanghai': 'Shanghai',
        'Asia/Singapore': 'Singapore', 'Asia/Bangkok': 'Bangkok',
        'Asia/Dubai': 'Dubai', 'Australia/Sydney': 'Sydney',
      };
      var city = tzCity[tz] || tz.split('/').pop().replace('_', ' ');

      var tokyoMsg = tokyoH >= 22 || tokyoH <= 5
        ? '\ud83c\udf19 Prime jet lag hours in Tokyo right now.'
        : tokyoH <= 8 ? '\ud83c\udf05 Early morning in Tokyo.'
        : '\ud83d\uddfc Tokyo is fully awake.';

      if (dom.visitorClock) {
        dom.visitorClock.innerHTML =
          '<span style="color:#7070a0">Your time (' + city + '):</span>' +
          '<span style="color:#e8e8f0; font-weight:600"> ' + fmtLocal + '</span><br>' +
          '<span style="color:#7070a0">Tokyo time:</span>' +
          '<span style="color:#00f0ff; font-weight:600; text-shadow: 0 0 8px #00f0ff44;"> ' + fmtTokyo + '</span><br>' +
          '<span style="color:#bf00ff; font-size:0.65rem;">' + tokyoMsg + '</span>';
      }
    })();

    // ─── CANVAS: WINDOW LIGHTS + NEON STREAKS ───
    var canvas = dom.cityCanvas;
    var ctx = canvas ? canvas.getContext('2d') : null;

    function resizeCanvas() {
      if (!canvas) return;
      canvas.width = canvas.offsetWidth;
      canvas.height = canvas.offsetHeight;
    }
    resizeCanvas();
    window.addEventListener('resize', resizeCanvas);

    if (!prefersReducedMotion && ctx) {
      var windows = [];
      var WINDOW_COUNT = 100;
      var COLORS = ['#00f0ff', '#bf00ff', '#ff0080', '#ffe000', '#ffffff', '#ff6600'];

      for (var i = 0; i < WINDOW_COUNT; i++) {
        windows.push({
          x: Math.random(), y: 0.35 + Math.random() * 0.55,
          w: 2 + Math.random() * 5, h: 2 + Math.random() * 4,
          color: COLORS[Math.floor(Math.random() * COLORS.length)],
          alpha: Math.random(), speed: 0.002 + Math.random() * 0.015,
          phase: Math.random() * Math.PI * 2,
          offChance: Math.random() < 0.3, offTimer: 0,
          offDuration: 60 + Math.random() * 200,
        });
      }

      var streaks = [];
      var STREAK_COUNT = 6;

      function createStreak() {
        var isH = Math.random() < 0.4;
        return {
          x: Math.random(), y: 0.5 + Math.random() * 0.5,
          length: 0.05 + Math.random() * 0.15,
          speed: (0.001 + Math.random() * 0.003) * (Math.random() < 0.5 ? 1 : -1),
          color: COLORS[Math.floor(Math.random() * 3)],
          alpha: 0, fadeIn: true,
          maxAlpha: 0.3 + Math.random() * 0.5,
          fadeSpeed: 0.008 + Math.random() * 0.015,
          horizontal: isH, done: false,
        };
      }

      for (var j = 0; j < STREAK_COUNT; j++) streaks.push(createStreak());

      function drawFrame() {
        ctx.clearRect(0, 0, canvas.width, canvas.height);
        var W = canvas.width, H = canvas.height;

        for (var i = 0; i < windows.length; i++) {
          var w = windows[i];
          if (w.offChance && w.offTimer > 0) { w.offTimer--; continue; }
          if (w.offChance && Math.random() < 0.0005) { w.offTimer = w.offDuration; continue; }
          w.phase += w.speed;
          var a = (Math.sin(w.phase) * 0.4 + 0.6) * 0.9;
          ctx.save();
          ctx.globalAlpha = a;
          ctx.fillStyle = w.color;
          ctx.shadowColor = w.color;
          ctx.shadowBlur = 4;
          ctx.fillRect(w.x * W, w.y * H, w.w, w.h);
          ctx.restore();
        }

        for (var k = 0; k < streaks.length; k++) {
          var s = streaks[k];
          if (s.done) { streaks[k] = createStreak(); continue; }
          if (s.fadeIn) { s.alpha += s.fadeSpeed; if (s.alpha >= s.maxAlpha) s.fadeIn = false; }
          else { s.alpha -= s.fadeSpeed * 0.5; if (s.alpha <= 0) { s.done = true; continue; } }
          s.x += s.speed;
          if (s.x < -s.length || s.x > 1 + s.length) s.done = true;
          var x1 = s.x * W, y1 = s.y * H, len = s.length * W;
          ctx.save();
          ctx.globalAlpha = s.alpha;
          var grad = ctx.createLinearGradient(x1, y1, s.horizontal ? x1 + len : x1, s.horizontal ? y1 : y1 + len * 0.3);
          grad.addColorStop(0, 'transparent');
          grad.addColorStop(0.3, s.color);
          grad.addColorStop(0.7, s.color);
          grad.addColorStop(1, 'transparent');
          ctx.strokeStyle = grad;
          ctx.lineWidth = 1.5;
          ctx.shadowColor = s.color;
          ctx.shadowBlur = 8;
          ctx.beginPath();
          if (s.horizontal) { ctx.moveTo(x1, y1); ctx.lineTo(x1 + len, y1); }
          else { ctx.moveTo(x1, y1); ctx.lineTo(x1 + len * 0.1, y1 + len * 0.3); }
          ctx.stroke();
          ctx.restore();
        }

        requestAnimationFrame(drawFrame);
      }
      drawFrame();
    }

    // ─── WORLD CLOCK ───
    function updateClocks() {
      var now = new Date();
      var fmt = function(tz) {
        return new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
          hour: '2-digit', minute: '2-digit', hour12: false, timeZone: tz
        }).format(now);
      };
      var hr = function(tz) {
        return parseInt(new Intl.DateTimeFormat('en-US', {
          hour: 'numeric', hour12: false, timeZone: tz
        }).format(now));
      };

      var cities = [
        { id: 'tokyo',  tz: 'Asia/Tokyo' },
        { id: 'la',     tz: 'America/Los_Angeles' },
        { id: 'nyc',    tz: 'America/New_York' },
        { id: 'london', tz: 'Europe/London' },
      ];

      cities.forEach(function(c) {
        var timeEl = document.getElementById('time-' + c.id);
        var statusEl = document.getElementById('status-' + c.id);
        if (!timeEl || !statusEl) return;
        timeEl.textContent = fmt(c.tz);
        var h = hr(c.tz);
        var sleeping = h >= 23 || h < 6;
        if (c.id === 'tokyo') {
          var jetlagged = h >= 1 && h <= 5;
          statusEl.textContent = jetlagged ? '\ud83c\udf19 Prime jet lag hours' : h >= 6 && h < 10 ? '\ud83c\udf05 Early morning' : '\ud83d\uddfc Normal hours';
          statusEl.className = 'clock-city-status status-awake';
        } else {
          statusEl.textContent = sleeping ? '\ud83d\ude34 Probably asleep' : '\u2600\ufe0f Awake back home';
          statusEl.className = 'clock-city-status ' + (sleeping ? 'status-sleep' : 'status-awake');
        }
      });
    }
    updateClocks();
    setInterval(updateClocks, 30000);

    // ─── PARTICLES ───
    if (!prefersReducedMotion && dom.particles) {
      var frag = document.createDocumentFragment();
      for (var i = 0; i < 12; i++) {
        var p = document.createElement('div');
        p.className = 'particle';
        p.style.left = Math.random() * 100 + '%';
        p.style.animationDuration = (8 + Math.random() * 15) + 's';
        p.style.animationDelay = (Math.random() * 15) + 's';
        p.style.setProperty('--drift', (Math.random() * 100 - 50) + 'px');
        if (Math.random() > 0.5) p.style.background = '#bf00ff';
        if (Math.random() > 0.7) p.style.background = '#ff0080';
        frag.appendChild(p);
      }
      dom.particles.appendChild(frag);
    }

    // ─── AREA NAVIGATION (EVENT DELEGATION) ───
    function scrollToArea(area, btnEl) {
      $$('.area-btn').forEach(function(b) {
        b.classList.remove('active');
        b.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'false');
      });
      btnEl.classList.add('active');
      btnEl.setAttribute('aria-pressed', 'true');

      var behavior = prefersReducedMotion ? 'auto' : 'smooth';
      if (area === 'all') {
        document.getElementById('venues').scrollIntoView({ behavior: behavior });
        $$('.area-section').forEach(function(s) { s.style.display = ''; });
      } else {
        $$('.area-section').forEach(function(s) { s.style.display = ''; });
        var target = document.getElementById('area-' + area);
        if (target) target.scrollIntoView({ behavior: behavior });
      }
    }

    // Event delegation on area nav
    if (dom.areaNav) {
      dom.areaNav.addEventListener('click', function(e) {
        var btn = e.target.closest('.area-btn');
        if (!btn) return;
        var area = btn.getAttribute('data-area');
        if (area) scrollToArea(area, btn);
      });

      // Keyboard navigation within toolbar
      dom.areaNav.addEventListener('keydown', function(e) {
        var btns = Array.from(dom.areaNav.querySelectorAll('.area-btn'));
        var idx = btns.indexOf(document.activeElement);
        if (idx === -1) return;
        if (e.key === 'ArrowRight' || e.key === 'ArrowDown') {
          e.preventDefault();
          btns[(idx + 1) % btns.length].focus();
        } else if (e.key === 'ArrowLeft' || e.key === 'ArrowUp') {
          e.preventDefault();
          btns[(idx - 1 + btns.length) % btns.length].focus();
        } else if (e.key === 'Home') {
          e.preventDefault();
          btns[0].focus();
        } else if (e.key === 'End') {
          e.preventDefault();
          btns[btns.length - 1].focus();
        }
      });
    }

    // ─── AREA NAV SCROLL INDICATORS ───
    function updateScrollIndicators() {
      var nav = dom.areaNav;
      var wrap = dom.areaNavWrap;
      if (!nav || !wrap) return;
      wrap.classList.toggle('can-scroll-left', nav.scrollLeft > 4);
      wrap.classList.toggle('can-scroll-right', nav.scrollLeft < nav.scrollWidth - nav.clientWidth - 4);
    }

    if (dom.areaNav) {
      dom.areaNav.addEventListener('scroll', updateScrollIndicators, { passive: true });
      window.addEventListener('resize', updateScrollIndicators);
      requestAnimationFrame(updateScrollIndicators);
    }

    // ─── TIME SLIDER ───
    var TIME_TIPS = {
      0:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: 'Midnight Ramen', body: 'Ichiran is open 24h. Nagi in Golden Gai is still going. The best bowls happen after midnight.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfee', title: 'Golden Gai', body: 'The tiny bars of Shinjuku are in full swing. Follow the noise down any alley.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\ude95', title: 'Last Train Warning', body: 'Last trains left 30 min ago. Open the GO or S.RIDE app now, or settle in until 5AM.' }],
      1:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: 'Deep Night Ramen', body: 'Nagi Shinjuku open until 7AM. Ichiran 24h. Afuri Roppongi until 5AM.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf03', title: 'Kabukicho Walk', body: 'The entertainment district never sleeps. Walk through for the spectacle.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfe7', title: 'Konbini Run', body: '7-Eleven has fresh onigiri. ATMs accept foreign cards. Coffee is always hot.' }],
      2:  [{ icon: '\u2668\ufe0f', title: 'Thermae-Yu Onsen', body: 'Open 24h in Shinjuku. A hot spring soak at 2AM is deeply restorative.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: "Ramen O'Clock", body: 'Peak ramen hour. Ichiran, Nagi, any open shop. You need this bowl.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf06', title: 'Empty Shibuya', body: "Walk to Shibuya crossing. Weekends it's alive. Weekdays: eerily beautiful." }],
      3:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udfd9\ufe0f', title: 'City of Ghosts', body: 'The streets are yours. Walk anywhere. The silence of Tokyo at 3AM is extraordinary.' },
           { icon: '\u2668\ufe0f', title: 'Night Onsen', body: "Thermae-Yu still open. You'll have the rotenburo almost to yourself." },
           { icon: '\u2615', title: 'Konbini Coffee', body: 'All convenience stores have freshly brewed coffee. \u00a5100. Surprisingly good.' }],
      4:  [{ icon: '\ud83d\ude9a', title: 'City Wakes Up', body: "Delivery trucks appear. Tsukiji outer market vendors start setup. Tokyo's other shift begins." },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf05', title: 'Pre-Dawn Walk', body: 'Head toward any park. The light before sunrise in Tokyo is unlike anywhere else.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf71', title: 'Early Breakfast', body: 'Some teishoku restaurants open at 5AM. Look for the ones with handwritten signs.' }],
      5:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf05', title: 'Sunrise Time', body: 'Ueno Park, Shinjuku Gyoen, Yoyogi. Any open green space will reward you now.' },
           { icon: '\u26e9\ufe0f', title: 'Meiji Shrine', body: 'Enter the forest before anyone else arrives. The morning rituals begin at dawn.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\ude83', title: 'First Trains', body: 'Yamanote Line restarts around 5AM. You can go anywhere again. The city resets.' }],
      6:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf73', title: 'Morning Set', body: 'Breakfast sets at kissaten coffee shops. Toast, egg, coffee for \u00a5500.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfef', title: 'Beat the Crowds', body: 'Senso-ji, Meiji Shrine, any temple. You have 2 hours before tour groups arrive.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\udc1f', title: 'Tsukiji Outer Market', body: 'Breakfast sushi and tamagoyaki at the outer market stalls. Open from 5-6AM.' }],
      7:  [{ icon: '\u2615', title: 'Coffee Culture', body: "Kissaten old-school coffee shops are at their best at 7AM. Order the morning set." },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf38', title: 'Park Walking', body: 'Tokyo parks are gorgeous in morning light. Locals exercise, feed birds, read.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\udecd\ufe0f', title: 'Early Konbini', body: 'Fresh deliveries just arrived. Best onigiri selection of the day is right now.' }],
      8:  [{ icon: '\ud83d\ude87', title: 'Rush Hour', body: 'Trains are packed. Avoid the subway 8-9AM if possible. Walk instead.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf71', title: 'Breakfast Done Right', body: 'Hotel breakfast or a neighborhood kissaten. Set yourself up for the day.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\uddfa\ufe0f', title: 'Morning Museums', body: 'National museums open at 9AM. First hour is almost empty.' }],
      9:  [{ icon: '\ud83c\udfdb\ufe0f', title: 'Museums Open', body: 'Tokyo National Museum, teamLab, Mori Art Museum. Pick one, go early.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\uded2', title: 'Department Stores', body: 'Depachika (basement food halls) open at 10AM. Worth a visit just to look.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf3f', title: 'Garden Time', body: 'Shinjuku Gyoen, Hamarikyu. Morning in a Japanese garden.' }],
      10: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udfd9\ufe0f', title: 'City in Full Swing', body: 'Everything is open. The most normal hour of the Tokyo day.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf63', title: 'Sushi Breakfast', body: 'Tsukiji outer market is still going. Toyosu market has tours and sushi.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\udcf8', title: 'Photography Hour', body: 'Morning light in Yanaka, Shimokitazawa, or Koenji.' }],
      11: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf71', title: 'Pre-Lunch Window', body: 'Best ramen shops open at 11AM and run out by early afternoon. Go now.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\udecd\ufe0f', title: 'Harajuku / Omotesando', body: 'Shops open, crowds manageable. Fashion district before afternoon rush.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfef', title: 'Last Quiet Temple Hour', body: 'By noon, tour groups arrive. Visit Asakusa now for breathing room.' }],
      12: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: 'Lunch Rush', body: 'Every ramen shop has a line. Avoid peak noon, eat at 11:30 or 1:30.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf33', title: 'Midday Park Break', body: 'Salary workers eat in parks. Join them. Konbini lunch outside.' },
           { icon: '\u2615', title: 'Afternoon Coffee', body: "Blue Bottle, Sarutahiko, Onibus \u2014 Tokyo's specialty coffee is excellent." }],
      13: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf8c', title: 'Afternoon Temples', body: 'Crowds thin slightly after lunch. Good time for a second temple visit.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfae', title: 'Akihabara', body: 'Electronics and anime district is fully alive in the afternoon.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf66', title: 'Soft Serve Tour', body: 'Matcha in Asakusa, sesame in Yanaka, wagyu in Ginza.' }],
      14: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udfec', title: 'Shibuya Scramble', body: 'Afternoon is good for Shibuya. Crowds manageable, shops open.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfa8', title: 'Art Galleries', body: 'Mori Art Museum, 21_21 Design Sight, or Ginza galleries.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfee', title: 'Planning Dinner', body: "Figure out where you're eating tonight. Popular places fill by 7PM." }],
      15: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf05', title: 'Golden Hour Prep', body: 'Position somewhere high or scenic before 5PM. Skytree, Roppongi Hills.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf75', title: 'Afternoon Tea', body: 'Hotel lobby bars and tea rooms are at their best mid-afternoon.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\uded2', title: 'Depachika Peak', body: 'Basement food halls fully stocked. Best selection of the day.' }],
      16: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf06', title: 'Golden Hour', body: 'Get to any elevated spot. Tokyo Tower, Skytree, or a rooftop terrace.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf7a', title: 'Happy Hour Starts', body: 'Standing bars (tachinomi) and izakayas start early deals. Beer from \u00a5300.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\udeb6', title: 'Evening Walk', body: 'Daikanyama, Nakameguro canal, or Shimokitazawa. Best in early evening.' }],
      17: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf05', title: 'Sunset Tokyo', body: 'Find the canal at Nakameguro or a shrine gate silhouette. Pure Tokyo.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf7a', title: 'After-Work Drinks', body: 'Salary workers descend on izakayas. Join the energy. Standing bar near any station.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf63', title: 'Pre-Dinner Sushi', body: 'Conveyor belt sushi before the dinner rush. Cheaper and still excellent.' }],
      18: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf56', title: 'Dinner Time', body: 'Yakitori under the train tracks, kushikatsu in a basement, or kaiseki if planned.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfee', title: 'Shinjuku Neon Wakes', body: 'Neon signs of Shinjuku fully illuminate after dark. Walk east from station.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfad', title: 'Evening Entertainment', body: "Kabuki, live music, standing comedy. Check what's on." }],
      19: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf7a', title: 'Izakaya Prime Time', body: 'Best hour at any izakaya. Groups are lively, food flowing, beer cold.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf03', title: 'Night Photography', body: 'Tokyo after dark is one of the most photogenic cities on earth.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfb6', title: 'Live Music', body: 'Shimokitazawa live houses. Shows typically start at 7-8PM.' }],
      20: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf76', title: 'Whisky Bar Time', body: "Japan's whisky culture shines in small bars. Try any quiet counter." },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf06', title: 'Night View', body: 'Tokyo at night from above. Skytree, observation decks, any tall building.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfb0', title: 'Pachinko Curiosity', body: 'Experience the sensory overload of a pachinko parlor. Uniquely Japanese.' }],
      21: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: 'Ramen for Dinner', body: 'Lines have calmed. Evening ramen at a proper shop before midnight rush.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfee', title: 'Golden Gai Warms Up', body: 'Tiny bars filling up. Good time to find your spot for the night.' },
           { icon: '\ud83d\ude83', title: 'Train Window', body: 'Take any JR line for a few stops at night. The city from the train is cinema.' }],
      22: [{ icon: '\ud83c\udf78', title: 'Bar Hopping Hour', body: 'Shinjuku, Roppongi, Shibuya or Shimokitazawa depending on energy.' },
           { icon: '\u23f0', title: 'Last Train Awareness', body: 'Last trains leave around midnight. Have GO or S.RIDE ready.' },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf03', title: 'Night Walk', body: 'The city is at its most cinematic 10PM\u20131midnight. Just walk.' }],
      23: [{ icon: '\ud83d\udd5b', title: 'Last Train Decision', body: "In the next hour: taxi home (open GO app) or stay until 5AM. Commit." },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udf5c', title: 'Midnight Ramen Pre-Load', body: "Eat ramen now before the midnight rush. You'll be glad you did." },
           { icon: '\ud83c\udfee', title: 'Night Owls Gathering', body: "The people left out at midnight chose to be here. The nocturnal crowd emerges." }],
    };

    function renderTimeTips(hour) {
      var h = parseInt(hour);
      var tips = TIME_TIPS[h] || TIME_TIPS[0];
      var pad = function(n) { return String(n).padStart(2, '0'); };
      if (dom.sliderDisplay) dom.sliderDisplay.textContent = pad(h) + ':00';

      if (dom.timeTipCards) {
        dom.timeTipCards.innerHTML = tips.map(function(t) {
          return '<div class="tip-card">' +
            '<div class="tip-card-icon" aria-hidden="true">' + t.icon + '</div>' +
            '<div class="tip-card-title">' + t.title + '</div>' +
            '<div class="tip-card-body">' + t.body + '</div>' +
            '</div>';
        }).join('');
      }
    }

    function setTokyoNow() {
      var h = getTokyoHour();
      if (dom.timeSlider) {
        dom.timeSlider.value = h;
        dom.timeSlider.setAttribute('aria-valuenow', h);
        dom.timeSlider.setAttribute('aria-valuetext', String(h).padStart(2,'0') + ':00 Tokyo time');
      }
      renderTimeTips(h);
    }

    if (dom.timeSlider) {
      dom.timeSlider.addEventListener('input', function(e) {
        var val = e.target.value;
        e.target.setAttribute('aria-valuenow', val);
        e.target.setAttribute('aria-valuetext', String(val).padStart(2,'0') + ':00 Tokyo time');
        renderTimeTips(val);
      });
    }

    if (dom.tokyoNowBtn) {
      dom.tokyoNowBtn.addEventListener('click', setTokyoNow);
    }

    setTokyoNow();

  })();
  </script>
</body>
</html>
